    "description": "<p>Come work with <a href=\"http://clareo.com\">Clareo</a>!</p>\n\n<p>We are growth strategists whose mission is to help leaders adapt their businesses and create new ways to grow in rapidly changing markets. Together, we build the plans and capabilities that deliver results. Our clients choose Clareo to improve strategy execution, find radical efficiency gains, develop entrepreneurial capabilities, bring new ideas to market, explore plausible futures, and invest in business ecosystems.</p>\n\n<p>Our suite of software tools empowers the work of innovation leaders with a proven approach. It is based on our own FastPath methodology, delivering powerful outcomes for our clients for over 15 years.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for a super talented Software QA Engineer who can optimize our software products for our clients. You will be a key member of the Clareo Software team but should be comfortable working independently as well. You are collaborative, curious and a creative problem solver when it comes to investigating and resolving software defects and bugs. </p>\n\n<p>Your responsibilities will include but not be limited to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Participate in release planning</li>\n<li>Create feature requirements and test documentation</li>\n<li>Work with the support team to address immediate needs</li>\n<li>Assist in general technical help for support requests</li>\n<li>Make adjustments necessary for client needs</li>\n<li>Help onboard new clients</li>\n<li>Perform hot-fixes to production code</li>\n<li>Perform QA on new development during release cycles</li>\n<li>Review code to insure accuracy and standards</li>\n<li>Write and execute test suites</li>\n<li>UI and UX review and testing</li>\n<li>Cross browser testing</li>\n<li>Contribute code to small features and bug fixes as part of the release cycles</li>\n<li>Help the team maintain coding standards by continually reviewing, optimizing, and refactoring the code base</li>\n</ul><p>Qualifications include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>BS in Computer Science or the equivalent in work experience</li>\n<li>Background in HTML, CSS, and Javascript</li>\n<li>Experience working with Node.js applications</li>\n<li>Experience with databases like PostgresSQL, MongoDB, MySQL, etc.</li>\n<li>Experience with front-end JS frameworks like Backbone, React, Vue, Ember, etc.</li>\n<li>Experience with HTML, including templating languages like Underscore, Handlebars, Jade, etc.</li>\n<li>Experience with CSS, including the use of preprocessors like Sass, Less, Stylus, PostCSS, etc.</li>\n<li>Understand of Git and Git workflows.</li>\n<li>Understanding of REST API architecture</li>\n<li>Experience writing tests and using test suites like Mocha, Chai, etc. </li>\n<li>QA experience with enterprise-level software </li>\n<li>Experience executing QA across multiple browsers</li>\n<li>Ability to document and troubleshoot errors</li>\n<li>Analytical mind with problem-solving aptitude</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills</li>\n<li>Great team player but also able to work independently</li>\n<li>Strong work ethic</li>\n<li>Flexibility, adaptability</li>\n</ul>",
