    "title": "Full Stack Ruby on Rails Engineer",
    "location": "Birmingham, Alabama",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>ProctorU is seeking a <strong>Full Stack Ruby on Rails Engineer</strong> to join our Development team and do amazing things. We need someone who is adept at understanding challenges and issues brought to us by ProctorU Staff and our institutions that can be creatively solved with technology. </p>\n\n<p><strong>We’re looking for our engineer to:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Be a team player</strong> by creatively communicating and collaborating with colleagues on best practices regarding our internal and external web applications. We’re not just a motley group of rockstars doing their own thing. We are the strongest when we work together and provide meaningful feedback to each other and share our knowledge. Success is measured by the shared results of the team.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Do it differently</strong> by not being afraid to make suggestions to improve our processes and the user experience. </li>\n<li>\n<strong>Make it Amazing</strong> by exhibiting a passion for creative solutions to keep us moving forward. We’re not just a website for taking tests. We are the leaders of the industry’s most advanced AI-based proctoring solution! </li>\n<li>\n<strong>Be a technical mentor</strong> by connecting the right people and cultivating our internal talent through sharing experiences and providing guidance.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>You will be responsible for:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Collaborating with Product Management, Sales, Operations,, and Marketing to identify and uncover customer business goals, needs, and pains, and work to show how ProctorU can address them</li>\n<li>Working with Implementation Teams to ensure early customer success and a long-term business relationship</li>\n<li>Proving the technical feasibility of the ProctorU platform to highly technical and developer audiences</li>\n<li>Staying on top of industry news, technology products, platforms and partners to ensure and provide and maintain a deep industry and ecosystem expertise</li>\n<li>Identifying areas of potential improvement in our sales efforts, and then work to improve them. This could be high level strategy, daily tactical efforts, or down in the weeks of creating documentation or how-to videos</li>\n<li>Custom developing and launching of new sales products and customer integrations to our internal teams and customer community</li>\n<li>Partnering closely with our customer success teams to ensure continuity of an amazing customer experience - for life</li>\n<li>Collaborating  closely with Product and Engineering teams to help influence product roadmap based on market/customer requirements</li>\n<li>Providing technical responses to RFPs and RFIs</li>\n</ul><p><strong>You should have the following experience:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Solving business problems through a technical solution; understanding technology value propositions</li>\n<li>Demonstrating a proven capacity to quickly absorb new concepts and technologies</li>\n<li>Spending a decent amount of time using and scripting WHAT LANGUAGE</li>\n<li>Working with Git and GitHub specifically</li>\n<li>Throwing together an app or to in a high level programming language</li>\n<li>Actively and honestly discussing product, company abilities and limitations in a way where we do not oversell or overpromise a solution</li>\n<li>Understanding of operations and infrastructure knowledge especially as it relates to networking and security<br>\n</li>\n</ul><p><strong>In addition to the above, our Engineer Rockstar should have  3-5 years of technical experience and knowledge of:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Full stack web development experience using Ruby on Rails, Ruby,  JavaScript (with React) and SCSS.</li>\n<li>Developing responsive and user-friendly web interfaces using modern frontend frameworks</li>\n<li>Test Driven Development (TDD) </li>\n<li>Database Design and Architecture</li>\n<li>PostgreSQL query optimization</li>\n<li>Database Infrastructure Scaling</li>\n</ul><p><strong>About Us</strong>\nHeadquartered in Birmingham, AL, ProctorU is the leading authority for online identity and knowledge verification. We help create trust in the knowledge earned online through professional-grade proctoring and multi-factor identity verification. Our premium services are designed to dissuade cheating by combining the benefits of technology, highly-specialized training and personal presence. We administer 3,000,000 exams annually with over 1,000 institutions in 129 countries. <em>Find out more at <a href=\"http://www.proctoru.com\">www.proctoru.com</a>!</em></p>\n\n<p>We are proud to state that we have the industry’s most advanced, fully-automated AI-based online proctoring solution which learns and adapts to test-taker behavior over time, making it smarter with each exam proctored. <em>Find our more at <a href=\"http://www.proctoru.com/proctoru-auto\">www.proctoru.com/proctoru-auto</a>!</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>About our Development Team</strong> \nOur ProctorU Engineering &amp; Design team gets to innovate and experiment daily with some of the latest technologies in our industry for a product that is paving the way in our space. </p>\n\n<p>We are always looking for opportunities to learn, grow, and have fun with one another. Our team has a fun environment that encourages individuality, collaboration, and creative problem solving. On top of that, we have our own ping-pong table, Xbox, PlayStation, and Basketball hoop!  Lastly, if you have a dog, why not bring them to the office? Find out more at <em><a href=\"https://www.proctoru.com/proclife/engineering/\">https://www.proctoru.com/proclife/engineering/</a>!</em></p>\n\n<p><strong>Why Work for us?</strong>\nWe are an innovative, nimble, and driven company with a high level of integrity. We work collaboratively to achieve shared goals which creates an environment of cross functional trust and dependability. And we like to have fun, too! From Holiday parties to celebrating birthdays to video game nights, we make sure to balance the hard work and dedication with some company fun time. </p>\n\n<p><strong>We also offer great benefits which includes:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Health, Dental, &amp; Vision Insurance with generous employer funding for employees and dependents;</li>\n<li>Flexible Spending Accounts</li>\n<li>Health Savings Account with generous employer funding</li>\n<li>401(k) plan with company matching</li>\n<li>Company-sponsored short-term and long-term disability plans</li>\n<li>Company-sponsored life insurance</li>\n<li>Company-subsidized pet insurance</li>\n<li>Perks program for corporate discounts on a variety of services and items</li>\n<li>Annual stipend (prorated for new hires) for qualified expenses such as student loan debt, gym membership, home gym equipment, child care costs, and/or educational expenses within line of work. </li>\n<li>Dog-friendly office</li>\n<li>Casual working environment</li>\n</ul><p><em>Apply by sending your resume to <a href=\"mailto:recruiter@proctoru.com\">recruiter@proctoru.com</a>!</em></p>",
    "how_to_apply": "<p>Email your resume with salary requirements to <a href=\"mailto:recruiter@proctoru.com\">recruiter@proctoru.com</a>!</p>",
