    "description": "<p><strong>MISSION</strong></p><p>\nTo design, implement, and create technical solutions to meet the current needs of the company with a focus on scalability to support future needs of the company.</p>\n\n<p><strong>DESCRIPTORS</strong></p><p>\nCode, Develop, Innovate, Design, Stabilize, Improve, Automate, Test, Debug</p>\n\n<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Support building and maintenance of company and event websites and coordinate with content writers during event launches<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Design and develop web applications including EMS (Sixthman’s custom built booking system), guest booking portal, and guest account management<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Support iPhone and Android Apps<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Test code to ensure quality, stability, and zero impact to the rest of the system<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Support the technology needs of the company by improving reporting, automating manual processes, and coding solutions for accounting, guest services, and other departments<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Maintain Wheelhouse, CMS, and other internal documentation repositories<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Support Amazon Cloud AWS infrastructure – EC2, RDS, S3, Load balancer, AMI<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Document and communicate technology capabilities to educate others within the company<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Sail on several of the Company’s music festivals at sea annually and perform various duties onboard which could include ushering, guest services, box office, etc. with goal of providing world class experience to guests and artists and partners<p></p>\n</li>\n</ul><p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE</strong></p><p></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science required (or equivalent experience)<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>2+ years of web development experience<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>PHP, required<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>MySQL, required<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>JavaScript / jQuery / Ajax, required<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Version Control (Subversion or Git), required<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Understanding of UX / Usability, required<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Amazon Cloud AWS experience, preferred<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>MVC Framework (Cake or Zend), preferred<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Ability to keep information confidential required<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Strong problem solving/analytical skills<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Good verbal, written, and interpersonal skills<p></p>\n</li>\n<li>Ability to work under pressure, meet timelines on multiple projects simultaneously, and adapt to changes or challenges<p></p>\n</li>\n</ul><p><strong>DISCUSSIONS YOU LEAD</strong></p><p>\nYou work with our other developers to implement quality technical solutions to assist the team in meeting the company’s goals and needs. You ensure that your code meets company and coding standards and is reusable, modular, and documented for future use.</p>\n\n<p><strong>WHO LEADS YOU</strong></p><p>\nSr. Director of IT,GS, Launch &amp; Community</p>\n\n<p><strong>About Sixthman</strong></p>\n\n<p>Sixthman creates festivals at sea designed to set the stage for moments that make life rock!  Since 2001, Sixthman has pioneered themed cruise experiences, creating intimate shared encounters for bands, brands, and their fans. We are proud to be celebrating our 18th year and the accomplishment of executing 116 festivals, hosting over 250,000 guests for 1,000,000 days on vacation at sea, including our first European festivals at sea coming in 2019. Our world class hosts and artists include KISS, Kid Rock, John Mayer, Zac Brown Band, Train, Pitbull, Paramore, Florida Georgia Line, Diplo, Joe Bonamassa, Lynyrd Skynyrd, 311, Lyle Lovett, Barenaked Ladies, Sister Hazel and for brand partners such as Turner Classic Movies, VH1, Steven Van Zandt’s Renegade Circus, Walker Stalker Con, truTV and others along with Sixthman curated festivals, The Rock Boat and Cayamo! Our festivals at sea bring non-stop performances, artist collaborations and a truly immersive music vacation experience with fan/band interactions throughout the voyage and in port. Our home ports of call include New Orleans, Louisiana, Miami and Tampa, Florida and Barcelona, Spain with dream destinations to the Virgin Islands, Belize, Honduras, Mexico, The Bahamas, and upcoming Mediterranean ports.</p>",
    "how_to_apply": "<p>If you feel like you would be a great addition to the culture of Sixthman, then please send your resume and cover letter to <a href=\"mailto:resumes@sixthman.net\">resumes@sixthman.net</a> with \"Software Developer\" in the subject line.</p>",
