    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>SUSE is the leading commercial Enterprise Linux distribution vendor, and one of the major Open Source contributors. Eg, SUSE has about 20 subdomain kernel maintainers in Kernel project, and constantly contribute about 3% kernel code change every year. SUSE respects employee's flexibility on creativity and innovation toward the great business result. SUSE engineering team is a global team from different continents. SUSE has a wide field of advanced technology, and offers developers with an open and curious mind a great opportunity to grow and enhance their skills. SUSE is the advocate of open source and support employees to do presentation in various conferences worldwide.</p>\n\n<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n\n<p>For our SUSE Linux Enterprise product line, we are looking for a Linux developer to work on Linux High Availability Cluster Infrastructure Layer, eg, pacemaker, corosync, kronosnet, SCTP, distributed lock manager(DLM), SAP HANA scale-up/scale-out, and the related packaging. Your research and development work include(but not limited): to investigate various open source projects, and provide constructive reports toward the solution; to impletment product feature, fix bug, continous integration; actively engage the techinical discussion in open source communities, and contribute code to the upstream projects.</p>\n\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n\n<p> Must have solid Linux(Unix) experience.\nMust have solid C language experience.\nMust be fluent in reading and writing English.\nMust have networking protocol programming experience, eg. TCP/IP or alike.\nUnderstanding of concensus algorithms(paxos, raft), etcd is a big plus.\nExperience on Cluster/High Availability/Distributed system is a big plus.\nExperience on Linux packaging and/or customization is a big plus.\nExperience on git, github, gitlab, or alike is a big plus.\nPassion for open-source and knowledge of community principles and practices.\nGood troubleshooting and debugging skills to find the root cause.\nExcellent interpersonal and communication skills.\nSolid skills in writing high-quality, well-designed and well-documented code.\nSelf-motivated with discipline.\nPerseverance toward the problem resolution.\nFast learner for the cutting-edge technology.\nTeam work spirit with people with different personalities.</p>\n\n<p>If you are interested in this position, please send your Chinese and English resume to julie.ing@suse.com and zzhou@suse.com, which subject should include \"Linux Developer for Cluster Infrastructure\", thanks!\nPlease log on https://jobs.suse.com to search more jobs in SUSE</p>\n\n<p>What we offer:</p>\n\n<p>Positive and creative work environment with an international team\nA growing business that is at the forefront of bringing new offerings to the Linux community\nDirect contact with representatives of free/open source software projects worldwide\nContributions to pension insurance or capital life insurance\nA competitive remuneration package</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, software-defined infrastructure and application delivery solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 25 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. The lasting relationships we build allow us to adapt and deliver the smarter innovation they need to succeedótoday and tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nChina, Beijing (CNBEJ)\nTracking code\n2018344\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
