    "created_at": "Thu Jun 28 16:54:42 UTC 2018",
    "title": "SUSE Enterprise Storage Developer - Level 3 Support",
    "location": "Nuremberg, Germany or Prague, CZ",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>SUSE L3 is a globally distributed team of highly skilled Linux developers who evaluate, analyze and fix software defects reported by SUSE customers. The L3 team is responsible for defect-resolution in a wide rang e of SUSE products ,technologies and areas, from core kernel bugs to crashing webservers, from simple RAID arrays to distributed Ceph storage clusters.</p>\n\n<p>In the SUSE Enterprise Storage position, your focus will be o n analyzing and fixing software defects in Ceph (CephFS, RADOS Gateway, RBD).</p>\n\n<p>If you consider yourself a fast-learner, if you like varied tasks and enjoy solving  tricky technical problems, either on your own or in close cooperation with other excellent Linux engineers, and would like to deepen your knowledge of distributed parallel fault-tolerant filesystems, then you should apply for this position.</p>\n\n<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n\n<p>For our SUSE Linux Enterprise product line, we are looking for a Linux developer to work on Linux High Availability Cluster Storage Layer, eg, cluster block device(soft RAID/mdadm), cluster logical volume manager(LVM), cluster file system(OCFS2/GFS2), DRBD, distributed lock manager(DLM), and the related packaging. Your research and development work include(but not limited): to investigate various open source projects, and provide constructive reports toward the solution; to impletment product feature, fix bug, continous integration; actively engage the techinical discussion in open source communities, and contribute code to the upstream projects.</p>\n\n<p>Key responsibilities:</p>\n\n<p>Evaluation of customer-reported issues\nTechnical analysis of issues and bugs in SUSE software products with the main focus on issues related to Ceph\nCoordination of and active involvement in the bug-fixing process\nFixing code defects and publishing patches</p>\n \n\n<p>Required skills and experience:</p>\n\n<p>Very good knowledge of the C and C++ programming languages\nVery good knowledge of the Linux operating system\nGood knowledge of Linux debugging tools and techniques (system dumps, GDB, strace, ...)\nStrong communication, analytical and organizational skills\nStrong proficiency in English, both spoken and written\nAbility and willingness to quickly learn new technologies and work independently with minimal supervision</p>\n\n<p>Desired skills:</p>\n\n<p>Programmer's knowledge of the Linux Kernel\nAbility to contribute to opensource projects\nUnderstanding of openStack Cloud, especially the Swift component\nKnowledge of a scripting language (Python, Ruby, ...)\nKnowledge of RPM</p>\n\n<p>What we offer:</p>\n\n<p>Direct contact with representatives of free/open-source software projects worldwide\nOpportunity to participate in the development of bleeding-edge FLOSS projects\nPossibilities to travel to conferences and other company sites around the world\nWeekly-based flexible working time\nA fun, creative, friendly and informal working environment where how you think is far more important than what you wear</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, software-defined infrastructure and application delivery solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 25 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. The lasting relationships we build allow us to adapt and deliver the smarter innovation they need to succeedótoday and tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nGermany, Nuremberg (DENUE)\nTracking code\n2018252\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
