    "location": "Prague, Czech Republic",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>Are you interested in Linux and modern opensource technologies?\nWould you like to join a relaxed environment of people ensuring Linux high quality standards?\nHave you ever worked in the Linux area? (as an admin for example)\nHave you ever tried or contributed to any opensource projects?\nHave you ever written code in bash, perl, python which you can present?\nHave you ever worked in a team where communication is key?\nAre you using English in different areas of life?\nAre you looking for opportunities to perform and grow within technologies like</p>\n\n<p>Containers\nKubernetes\nopenQA\nOpensource virtualization\nSalt, Ansible\nJenkins\nOpenStack\nand much more</p>\n\n<p>Then there is a high chance you are a perfect fit for our Maintenance QA team.</p>\n\n<p>What? Quality Assurance? Yes, it may sound boring. But not in our case. When you are enthusiatic about configuring challenging Linux and other opensource technology setups, and learning and testing their abilities, then please note that this will be the major part of your work.\nStill interested? So lets take a look at what we can offer:</p>\n\n<p>Key responsibilities:</p>\n\n<p>Manual testing of various components of our products\nWork on the opensource automation frameworks like openQA and jenkins\nWorking on cross-team development and implementation of QA testing and automation\nDesigning, developing and maintaining of manual and automated tests\nMaintenance of reference test systems\nPerforming related documentation tasks</p>\n\n<p>Something on top of that:</p>\n\n<p>we are not setting borders - once you know how to do things better, please do so\nwe are contributing to opensource\nyou will have a chance to show off (hackweeks)\nwe are an environment of technology enthusiasts\nwe are flexible (when you are tired about early morning wake-ups for example)\nwe also travel a bit (chance to participate in conferences, meetups, exchange programs, trainings)</p>\n\n<p>And a little bit more:</p>\n\n<p>https://events.opensuse.org/\nhttps://www.opensuse.org/\nhttps://www.facebook.com/SUSEWorldwide/</p>\n\n<p>Candidate Profile:</p>\n\n<p>WGood knowledge of the Linux operating system (experience in Linux system administration, system programming is desirable)\nProgramming skills in Python/Perl and a desire to improve them\nInterest in the automation area\nDedication to improvement and innovation in testing and automation\nEnglish written and spoken\nInvolvement in opensource projects is a plus\nAnalytical mindset\nReliable; able to work independently and as part of the team\nCommunication skills\nAvailability to occasionally travel internationally between different R&amp;D sites if needed</p>\n\n<p>And what \"green\" people think about SUSE:</p>\n\n<p>\"Working for SUSE so far has been the best choice I ever made in my job career. The working environment is great and I am happy to be surrounded by people that support each other and work in team spirit to bypass any potential challenges.\"</p>\n\n<p>\"SUSE has a unique opensource oriented culture. Employees are encouraged to participate in community efforts.\"</p>\n\n<p>\"SUSE offices are a friendly open environment with smart people inside. The company provides a challenging job which combines enterprise requirements with opensource.\"</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, software-defined infrastructure and application delivery solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 25 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. The lasting relationships we build allow us to adapt and deliver the smarter innovation they need to succeedótoday and tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nCzech Republic, Prague (CZPRG01)\nTracking code\n2018060\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
