    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE weíre building the next-generation cloud platforms based on Kubernetes and Cloud Foundry. The SUSE Cloud Application Platform engineering team is looking for a Software Engineer to join us on the journey in designing and building these platforms. You will be contributing to the Cloud Foundry open source project and delivering the world's best enterprise grade application hosting platform. This makes software developer's lifes easier and enables them to deliver better software faster.</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE we're strongly committed to open source and contribute to numerous free and open projects and initiatives. We embrace and believe in the open source innovation model and the open source business model. As a member of the SUSE Cloud Application Platform team you will have the opportunity to contribute to and be part of various open source projects like Cloud Foundry, Kubernetes, and Helm. You will work together with the communities for these projects and strive to continuously advance the state of the art to meet customer requirements.</p>\n\n<p>We're looking for someone who loves to dabble in everything from automation, to systems engineering, to operations ñ someone who enjoys working on complex problems, and isnít afraid to span the stack from network architecture all the way to coding on Kubernetes. You should have an analytical mind, experience with basic computer science concepts and best practices, and a keen interest to learn new things.</p>\n\n<p>Curiosity and good teamwork are two of the values that drive us as an engineering team. If you are passionate about these values too, you are likely a great fit for us. As a team, we're constantly finding new ways to improve ourselves. One way we do this is by hosting regular FOSS-themed ìhack weeks,î where all developers (and we mean it) are encouraged to work on any project of their choosing, either individually or as a team. We pride ourselves on our communication and teamwork - we're all in this together!</p>\n\n<p>If you bring hands-on experience building complex distributed systems and API driven web services or with technologies such as Docker, Kubernetes and Go that's great. But we expect you to enjoy learning new things as well as you can expect us to provide plenty of opportunity to learn.</p>\n\n<p>Come join us if you want to be part of this.</p>\n\n<p>What you can expect from us:</p>\n\n<p>Working in a team which lives and breathes open source and Linux\nA balance of freedom and responsibility which allows you to take charge of your work\nWorking on projects that matter, which are mission-critical for our customers\nAn environment and colleagues which help you to learn, to grow, and to have fun\nTwo Hack Weeks a year, where you are free to work on projects of your choice</p>\n\n<p>What we expect from you:</p>\n\n<p>Hands-on software development experience in a variety of programming languages\nExperience and/or interest in Agile methodologies\nExperience and/or interest in Test Driven Development (TDD)\nExperience of working in Linux based environments\nExperience working on production, shipping code\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\nAbility to effectively communicate product architectures and design proposals</p>\n\n<p>Bonus qualifications:</p>\n\n<p>Knowledge of Cloud Foundry, OpenShift, Kubernetes, Apache Mesos, Docker containers\nKnowledge of, or desire to learn, Go, Ruby\nExperience with open source development\nExperience with Cloud Computing (OpenStack, AWS, or Azure) and/or Distributed Systems\nExperience working with a distributed team. We are a diverse team and you will engage with team members across many time zones and cultures.</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, software-defined infrastructure and application delivery solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 25 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. The lasting relationships we build allow us to adapt and deliver the smarter innovation they need to succeedótoday and tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nGermany, Nuremberg (DENUE)\nTracking code\n2017925\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
