    "description": "<p>Senior Software Engineer</p>\n\n<p>University of Notre Dame</p>\n\n<p>The University of Notre Dame (<a href=\"http://ND.jobs\">http://ND.jobs</a>) is accepting applications for a Senior Software Engineer.</p>\n\n<p>Applications will be accepted until 7/20/2018.</p>\n\n<p>Job Description</p>\n\n<p>In 2017 Notre Dame Ranks 11th Among Large Organizations in IDG's Computerworld 2017 Best Places to Work in IT : <a href=\"https://oit.nd.edu/latest/nd-ranks-in-computerworld-2017-best-places-to-work/\">https://oit.nd.edu/latest/nd-ranks-in-computerworld-2017-best-places-to-work/</a></p>\n\n<p>For the seventh consecutive year, the University of Notre Dame has been named a Great College to Work For by the Chronicle of Higher Education's annual “Great Colleges to Work For” survey… and we are proud of it!</p>\n\n<p>The Hesburgh Libraries' Sr. Software Engineer plays a central role in the ability of the library to cater technical solutions to the needs of the university in its mission to advance scholarship, learning and research. This position is responsible for designing reliable back end data services, web based applications and infrastructure which anticipates the evolving information needs of students and faculty members. Responsibilities include the design and implementation of scalable applications and software components, as well as engagement with library constituents in negotiating the diverse research and learning needs of the university. Incumbents are also expected to implement industry best practices and standards. The position requires a high degree of accountability, as well as the ability to manage project time lines, deliverables, and resources to ensure that planned objectives are met.</p>\n\n<p>Duties include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Design, implement, test, deploy and support a wide range of software applications in support of core library objectives.</p></li>\n<li><p>Architect and implement robust and dependable infrastructure components, data services, and software integration services.</p></li>\n<li><p>Engage with library faculty and staff, as well as product and service owners in order to define requirements</p></li>\n<li><p>Work independently, update appropriate documentation, and work with quality assurance and usability professionals.</p></li>\n</ul><p>Minimum Qualifications</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><p>Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience</p></li>\n<li><p>Minimum 2 - 4 years experience (with BA or BS degree)</p></li>\n<li><p>Knowledge of programming techniques and best practices, as well as how to test and deploy applications</p></li>\n<li><p>Preferred candidates will have some experience using cloud based deployment and orchestration tools such as AWS or Google Cloud</p></li>\n<li><p>High degree of experience with web technologies and standards such as HTML, CSS and Javascript</p></li>\n<li><p>Strong knowledge of object oriented design and development</p></li>\n<li><p>Experience with web based APIs</p></li>\n<li><p>Systems integration skills</p></li>\n<li><p>Use of version control system such as git</p></li>\n<li><p>Strong verbal and written skills</p></li>\n</ul><p>Department Hesburgh Libraries (28120)</p>\n\n<p>Department Website library.nd.edu</p>\n\n<p>Family / Sub-Family IT / Apps Dvlpmt</p>\n\n<p>Career Stream/Level EIC 2 Professional</p>\n\n<p>Department Hiring Pay Range $60,000 - $79,000</p>\n\n<p>Pay ID Semi-Monthly</p>\n\n<p>FLSA Status S1 - FT Exempt</p>\n\n<p>Job Category Information Technology</p>\n\n<p>Job Type Full-time</p>\n\n<p>Schedule: Days of Week &amp; Hours. 8 - 5, Monday - Friday</p>\n\n<p>Schedule: Hours/Week 40</p>\n\n<p>Schedule: # of months 12</p>\n\n<p>Posting Detail Information</p>\n\n<p>The University of Notre Dame seeks to attract, develop, and retain the highest quality faculty, staff and administration. The University is an Equal Opportunity Employer, and is committed to building a culturally diverse workplace. We strongly encourage applications from female and minority candidates and others that will enhance our community. Moreover, Notre Dame prohibits discrimination against veterans or disabled qualified individuals, and requires affirmative action by covered contractors to employ and advance veterans and qualified individuals with disabilities in compliance with 41 CFR 60-741.5(a) and 41 CFR 60-300.5(a).</p>\n\n<p>Job Posting Date (Campus) 06/27/2018</p>\n\n<p>Job Posting Date (Public) 06/27/2018</p>\n\n<p>Job Closing Date 07/20/2018</p>\n\n<p>Posting Type Open To All Applicants</p>\n\n<p>Posting Number S18544</p>\n\n<p>ABOUT NOTRE DAME:\nThe University of Notre Dame, founded in 1842 by Rev. Edward F. Sorin, C.S.C., of the Congregation of Holy Cross, is an independent, national Catholic university located in Notre Dame, Ind. For the fifth consecutive year, the University of Notre Dame has received Honor Roll distinctions as one of the top 10 higher education workplaces in the country in the Chronicle of Higher Education's annual \"Great Colleges to Work For\" survey...and we are proud of it!</p>\n\n<p>The University of Notre Dame seeks to attract, develop, and retain the highest quality faculty, staff and administration. The University is an Equal Opportunity Employer, and is committed to building a culturally diverse workplace. We strongly encourage applications from female and minority candidates and others that will enhance our community. Moreover, Notre Dame prohibits discrimination against veterans or disabled qualified individuals, and requires affirmative action by covered contractors to employ and advance veterans and qualified individuals with disabilities in compliance with 41 CFR 60-741.5(a) and 41 CFR 60-300.5(a).</p>",
