    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE weíre building the next-generation cloud platforms based on Kubernetes and Cloud Foundry. The SUSE Cloud Application Platform engineering team is looking for a Software Engineer to join us  on the journey in designing and building these platforms.You will be actively contributing to the Cloud Foundry open source project and delivering the world's best enterprise grade application hosting platform.</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE we're strongly committed to open source and contribute to numerous free and open projects and initiatives. We embrace and believe in the open source innovation model and the open source business model. As a member of the SUSE Cloud Application Platform team you will have the opportunity to contribute to and be part of various open source projects like Cloud Foundry, Kubernetes, and Helm. You will work together with the communities for these projects and strive to continuously advance the state of the art to meet customer requirements.</p>\n\n<p>Curiosity and good teamwork are two of the values that drive us as a development team. If you are passionate about these values too, you are likely a great fit for us. As a team, we're constantly finding ways to improve ourselves. We pride ourselves on our communication and teamwork ñ we're all in this together!</p>\n\n<p>Come join us if you have hands-on experience building complex distributed systems and API driven web services. A deep technical passion and enjoying learning the latest technologies and programming languages like Docker, Kubernetes and Go is a plus.</p>\n\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n\n<p>Education and Experience:</p>\n\n<p>Bachelor or Master's degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or equivalent experience</p>\n\n<p>Knowledge and Skills:</p>\n\n<p>At least 2 yearsí software engineering or equivalent experience:</p>\n\n<p>Hands-on software development experience in a variety of programming languages\nExperience and/or interest in Agile methodologies\nExcellent analytical and problem solving skills\nExperience of working in Linux based environments\nExperience working on production, shipping code\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\nAbility to effectively communicate product architectures and design proposals</p>\n\n<p>Bonus qualifications:</p>\n\n<p>Knowledge of Cloud Foundry, OpenShift, Kubernetes, Apache Mesos, Docker containers\nKnowledge of, or desire to learn, Go, Ruby, and Java\nPerformance instrumentation, analysis and tuning\nExperience and/or interest in Test Driven Development (TDD)\nExperience with open source development\nExperience with Cloud Computing (OpenStack, AWS, or Azure) and/or Distributed Systems\nExperience working with a distributed team. You will be expected to engage with team members across many time zones and cultures.</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, software-defined infrastructure and application delivery solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 25 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. The lasting relationships we build allow us to adapt and deliver the smarter innovation they need to succeedótoday and tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nCanada, Vancouver (CAVAN)\nTracking code\n2017895\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
