    "location": "Nuremberg, Germany",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE, we are passionate about Open Source and we are major contributors to many upstream projects. In our daily work, we value creativity and innovation, while staying focused on delivering business results. Our engineering team is a global team from almost all continents. SUSE has a wide field of advanced technologies and offers developers with an open and curious mind a great opportunity to apply and grow their skills.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for a candidate who is passionate about Linux and loves to work on automated installation of Linux systems. In your role as Automated Installation Engineer you will work with other technical  experts and engineers on improving SUSE's story on automated installation. Your job is to write program code which will automate system installation  steps accordingly.</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE we already have a set of even different tools to perform  automated system installation. Some address very specific requirements bound to a single product, other are more general in their scope. Together with your peers and technology architects you will work on  defining and building a consistent technology stack for this purpose.</p>\n\n<p>If you are ready to work on a fascinating technology which millions  of system administrators will be using, then you have found the right topic. Automated installations take place in many different contexts  ranging from public &amp; private cloud instances to on premise set ups and just local virtual machines. There are tremendous opportunities  to make a difference with your work at SUSE. We look forward to hear  from you.</p>\n\n<p>Expected skills:</p>\n\n<p>Bachelor degree in computer science and comparable\ngood Python coding skills\ngood knowledge of Linux (configuration, installation)\nBash scripting\nsolid command of English to communicate successfully in a professional environment\nprofessional attitude and team spirit</p>\n\n<p>Desired skills:</p>\n\n<p>good understanding of OS imaging technologies\nsolid know-how on system boot and init\nexperience with the Salt configuration management tool</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, software-defined infrastructure and application delivery solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 25 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. The lasting relationships we build allow us to adapt and deliver the smarter innovation they need to succeedótoday and tomorrow.</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nGermany, Nuremberg (DENUE)\nTracking code\n2017691\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
