    "location": "Nuremberg, Germany",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n\n<p>The SUSE Cloud Quality Assurance team plays a critical role in ensuring the overall quality of SUSE Cloud products based on OpenStack. This QA Engineer position is a development role. In this position, you will be responsible for creating and maintaining test plans, automation tools and scripts as well as analyzing and debugging issues reported against test infrastructure, tools and test cases. You will work along with other QA engineers in an international team, interfacing closely with product leaders and developers to fulfill these responsibilities.</p> \n\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n\n<p>Design, develop and document test plans, automation tools, features and test scripts\nExecute automated tests and analyze and report the results\nCreate documentation\nHandle and fix reported issues, where applicable. Work closely with the developer to troubleshoot new issues.\nProvide detailed reports for assigned tasks</p>\n\n<p>Required Skills and Experience:</p>\n\n<p>Strong OpenStack experience is required.\nLinux Administration experience is highly desired.\nProgramming skills.\nProficient in one or more scripting language (preferred PHP, Perl, Python, Bash)\nExperience in software development/engineering\nGood communication skills (English)\nStrong dedication to Quality\nPrior test automation or testing experience:\ntest automation\ntest specification\ntest documentation/reporting\ntest execution\nUnderstanding of the open source development model\nExperience with Cloud technologies\nQuick at learning and understanding new products and technologies\nAbility to work effectively as part of a global team across time zones</p>\n \n\n<p>Nice to have:</p>\n \n\n<p>Web development experience\nScrum experience\nExperience working in agile teams</p>\n\n<p>About SUSE</p>\n\n<p>SUSE, a pioneer in open source software, provides reliable, interoperable Linux, cloud infrastructure and storage solutions that give enterprises greater control and flexibility. More than 20 years of engineering excellence, exceptional service and an unrivaled partner ecosystem power the products and support that help our customers manage complexity, reduce cost, and confidently deliver mission-critical services. SUSE is also an active member of many open source communities, such as the openSUSE Project, OpenStack, Ceph, OpenNFV, OpenHPC, and more, to help drive collaboration among global communities to help solve some of the worldís most challenging technology issues.</p>\n\n<p>At SUSE, we set challenging goals for ourselves, then work to meet, and often exceed them. How far can you go with extraordinary colleagues at your side?</p>\n\n<p>For more information, visit www.suse.com</p>\n\n<p>Location:\nGermany, Nuremberg (DENUE)\nTracking code\n2017635\nPosition Type\nFull-Time/Regular</p>",
