    "location": "Chattanooga, TN",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>We are looking for a talented web developer to join our collaborative team at Spectruss! This person must have a broad knowledge of responsive website development and have the ability to adapt and problem solve outside of their normal realm of coding. They must also have the ability to work well with others, including our in-house creative team. </p>\n\n<p>A large number of our websites are built on WordPress, so a strong skill set in custom developing WordPress sites is a must. The applicant must also be comfortable in taking PSD files and transferring them to a responsive layout.  Additionally, having experience in the e-commerce realm is a must. This will include having experience and confidence in setting up payment processors and gateways, SSL encryption, adjusting / building server security, CMS security, and building / setting up UX for account and cart pages.  </p>\n\n<p>Lastly, we host many of our clients websites on our own server. The applicant must have experience in the following: development in a LAMP stack environment, management of DNS, installation / issuing SSL certs, maintaining an organized file management system, server security. </p>\n\n<p>Employee must work in house at Spectruss office in Chattanooga, TN, located in a beautifully restored building in Saint Elmo, at the bottom of Lookout Mountain. The building also features a Taproom, Coffee Shop, Yoga Studio and Climbing Gym. Laid back and inspiring working environment where employees can bring their dogs to work. Starting with  two weeks paid vacation, two weeks paid sick leave. Office hours from 9 am - 5pm with 1 hour lunch. Pay depends on experience and ability. </p>\n\n<p>Please reach out with any questions you may have. </p>\n\n<p>Thank you!</p>",
