    "title": "Principal Engineer/Technical Specialist - Software Systems - Automated Driving and Driver Assistance ",
    "location": "Plymouth, MI",
    "type": "Full Time",
    "description": "<p>As one of the largest North American automotive suppliers, Bosch develops, manufactures and supplies precision components and systems - including body electronics, chassis and powertrain products - for vehicle manufacturers worldwide. Since its foundation 1886, the company accelerates the progress of Automotive Technology with continued innovations. By choice, we are committed to a diverse workforce - EOE/Protected Veteran/Disabled.</p>\n\n<p>The Chassis Systems Control division develops and manufactures innovative components, functions and systems that are designed to make driving a safe and comfortable experience.  We are especially committed to developing sensors that observe vehicle surroundings and advancing new functions and systems that protect lives. In the future, we will network vehicles to other road users, infrastructure and the internet to ensure that our vision of accident and injury-free driving becomes a reality</p>\n\n<p>Robert Bosch LLC is looking for a Technical Specialist in our Plymouth, MI location. Our technical specialists are leadership positions and are expected to be the key technical contact for our customers, management and the different engineering teams. They come with 10+ years of problem solving experience and with an ability to pick up new tooling and new domains quickly and contribute back to the organization. They assist engineering management with strategic decisions and breaking down work-packages for our team of engineers.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>This position is focused on software and algorithm development in the domain on Autonomous Driving and Driving Assistance. Our team focusses on the building blocks of automated driving like perception, localization and trajectory planning. Besides Bosch proprietary tooling, we use the Robotic Operating System (ROS) for prototyping. Expertise in C++ and the ability to handle Linux/Ubuntu OS is expected for this position. </li>\n<li>Often, you will lead requirement elicitation activities with the customer (internal/external). While doing so, you should be able to handle functional and non functional requirements diligently.</li>\n<li>This position has a massive C++ codebase, and the right candidate must be willing to dive right in. You should be ready to work with system engineers to create scalable, maintainable and robust software designs for new driver assistance (ADAS) functions and/or automated driving (HAD, AD). Project are all SAE J3016 Level 3 and above.</li>\n</ul><p>Here are some of things you will be working on:\nAfter designing the prototype with the team, you will use formal methods to validate and verify your solutions.\nYou will be sometimes asked to make legacy code run faster to ensure our embedded device can handle all that computation. Of course, the customer and your manager will expect you to do this without any compromise in the system performance.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>You will be creating code based on complicated math and turn that into understandable, readable code.</li>\n<li>You will document (just enough) and version control the code to allow for easy walk-backs and sharing with other divisions in Bosch, local or international. You will be using version control (we use git in some complicated ways to bring in multiple repositories), issue tracking (we use JIRA)</li>\n<li>You will help set up test cases to ensure that the code is bullet-proof since we work on safety critical systems that revolve around human life. </li>\n<li>Besides being a good coder yourself, you will need to motivate everyone around you to code better. You're used  to being a servant leader and figuring out how to divide up the work, how to offer suggestions, and remove technical impediments.</li>\n<li>You will be writing code that's multi-platform (Linux, Windows and Embedded targets) and you'll need to be comfortable picking up whatever internal or open source libraries are needed to help you do it.</li>\n</ul><p>Qualifications:</p>\n\n<p>Basic Qualifications:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree or higher education in an engineering discipline.</li>\n<li>8+ years of academic or professional experience in software code, software architect and embedded control systems, including expert C++ skills. </li>\n<li>5+ years of working knowledge in other languages - Java or Python preferably.</li>\n</ul><p>Preferred Qualifications:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Aptitude for picking up new languages, as the job requires.</li>\n<li>Candidate will have a passion for innovation and a sophisticated understanding of software systems and applications.</li>\n<li>Knowledge of driver assistance sensor technologies and functions as well as vehicle electrical architecture.</li>\n<li>Exposure to Robotic Operating System (ROS)</li>\n<li>Excellent  communication skills to discuss issues / solutions with team and external customers.</li>\n<li>Capable to work independently in an organized and structured fashion.</li>\n<li>Comfortable with in-vehicle test activities Experience with Vector tools such as CANape and CANalyzer.</li>\n<li>Experience with designing state machines and scalable.</li>\n<li>Experience with automotive communication protocols such as CAN, LIN and Automotive Ethernet.</li>\n</ul>",
    "how_to_apply": "<p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:pranav.gandhi@randstadsourceright.com\">pranav.gandhi@randstadsourceright.com</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://jobs.smartrecruiters.com/BoschGroup/743999653900130-technical-specialist-software-systems-automated-driving-and-driver-assistance\">https://jobs.smartrecruiters.com/BoschGroup/743999653900130-technical-specialist-software-systems-automated-driving-and-driver-assistance</a></p>",
